caption: This is my TicTok made me do it. Big Frank's truck sits outside the Valor Brewpub. This bacon is AMAZING, it is cut thick & melts in your mouth. You must try the mac & cheese along with the ribs. I almost forgot the brisket, let's say oh my. All the meats are smoked to perfection. My family ate for 2 days & it's 3 of us. This will be my monthly treat, 2 slices of bacon with mac&cheese.

Ate here for the first time and will definitely be back soon.  The brisket is one of the best things I’ve had in a long time.  The beer selection is good, especially if you like dark beer or want a change from the usual IPA-heavy menus that are common in the DC area.  Staff are cool and the place has a really chill vibe.  Highly recommend.

Valor Brewpub is a brewpub that serves food and drinks. The brewpub is open daily from 11am to 2am but the kitchen hours varies per day.  After drinking in H Street Corridor, my friends and I wanted a change in environment so we came to Valor Brewpub, where we had house brewed beers, craft beers, and craft and barrel rested cocktails.  The bartender was friendly and knowledgeable about the cocktails. All of the barrel rested cocktails contained Journeyman Rye. Despite the Boulevardier being sweeter, I preferred the Old Fashioned.

Fun little place to hang out with friends and grab some good drinks.
Was going through a restructuring phase apparently, not sure how things have changed, but unbelievably sloooooow service there won't have me returning..

Went here to grab a drink on a Saturday night. Tables were mostly empty but a few people were enjoying drinks and food. Walked in an immediately was given a drink menu (great!). THEN we waited 20 minutes for someone to ask us if we wanted a drink. Finally recieved our drinks and began to enjoy the night. Then, when there was even fewer people there, we didn’t have someone follow up for 35 minutes, at which point we were long done our drinks and ready to go. We got our check and left. The gentleman who gave us our menu wished us well... from a block down the road!!! You should be in your restaurant assisting customers and not milling around on the street if you want tips. Would have loved a second beer because they were fantastic, but the service was so bad that I didn’t want to tip, and I generally give very generous tips. If you want good service, demand it instead of expecting normal satisfying service here.

Valor Brewpub is a small pub on Barracks Row that brews their own beer in house (you can watch them through the glass windows in the back). It opened to serve veterans and sits across from the historic barracks.  The space is small, but there's a bar in the front and tables throughout the narrow room. They have their own beer on the menu as well as other beer from across the country. They even make their own cocktails. If you like sweeter drinks, ask the bartender to make you their white sangria. It's so good and a healthy pour.  The food is good too. The fries come out hot, seasoned, and accompanied with flavored mayo. The fried rice is balanced and spicy. If you have a kid with you, the sausage bowl is perfect.  The service is on point and friendly.  They have TVs and will play anything on request.
chill atmosphere,  friendly staff,  and good drinks.

Very friendly atmosphere and great music. If you’re looking for a delicious meal that’s reasonably priced be sure to visit Valor pub and brewery. Well worth your time!!!

I haven't been to Barracks Row in awhile and found this place by accident while looking for the Ugly Mug before a show at the Miracle Theater. Same owner, and the Mug is still there, just moved upstairs.  The pilsner and stout were both well done, but needs another visit  (and star?) when they start brewing on location. Staff was quick and helpful. The chicken Cuban was delicious, and the roasted carrots in Old Bay made the meal.

I've now been here twice and both times have been superb. They brew their own beer and also carry several other local drafts. Very good selection. The vibe is very welcoming and feels like a cozy neighborhood bar.  The food is fantastic as well. I've had the Cuban as well as the tropic thunder wings and both were excellent. Excited to try their other items.  The service here has always been top notch. I had Liam as my bartender the first time and Tom the second. Both were very friendly, attentive, but never overbearing. They do a great job of making you feel welcome and helping you enjoy your time.  Overall, fantastic addition to Barracks Row. I look forward to coming back again.

Found this place on a Friday night after eating dinner elsewhere. They have been open for only a few weeks. Although their newness shows in the form of some growing pains (they ran out of limes on a Friday night with a moderate crowd), they have some solid fundamentals. They're focused on veterans and "Made in America" but they're  not in your face about it. Their cocktails are excellent, especially their French press concept. Basically they use a French press to crush fruit and herbs to infuse alcohol.  I assume others do it,  but thats the first I've seen it.  Overall,  we enjoyed ourselves and plan to visit again as they develop and start brewing their own beer.
